guage-text\">title</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">path</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">date</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">content</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">excerpt</code>, and <code class=\"language-text\">slug</code> are now custom fields.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Custom fields are no longer camel cased automatically.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Some plugins depends on the original field names to work properly.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Routes for pages in <code class=\"language-text\">src/pages</code> no longer get automatic names</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This was changed because automatic route names would most likely conflict with custom pages.</li>\n<li>Links like <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;g-link :to=&quot;{name: &#39;about&#39;}&quot;&gt;</code> needs to be updated to <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;g-link to=&quot;/about&quot;&gt;</code>. Or add a custom <code class=\"language-text\">name</code> to the Page.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"other-features-and-fixes\"><a href=\"#other-features-and-fixes\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Other features and fixes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Add custom node fields as top-level options. <a href=\"/docs/data-store-api#collectionaddnodeoptions\">Read more</a></li>\n<li>Limit argument for GraphQL. <a href=\"/docs/querying-data#limit\">Read more</a></li>\n<li>Advanced GraphQL sort argument. <a href=\"/docs/querying-data#advancedsorting\">Read more</a></li>\n<li>Configure webpack without chaining. <a href=\"/docs/config#configurewebpack\">Read more</a></li>\n<li>Render the current state in markup to prevent initial request.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You will find all the changes in the <a href=\"https://github.com/gridsome/gridsome/blob/master/gridsome/CHANGELOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">changelog</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"3000-github-stars-\"><a href=\"#3000-github-stars-\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>3000 GitHub Stars ðŸŒŸðŸŽ‰</h2>\n<p>Thanks to everyone who have contributed! Gridsome is going fast on its mission to be the best and easiest way to build modern websites and PWAs for any data source.</p>\n","author":[],"excerpt":"Gridsome 0.6 introduces a Pages API that gives you full control of page creation. It also has an API that lets you fetch internal pages into other pages and components. This is perfect for lightboxes or Â«Click for moreÂ» pagination etc. 0.6 also improves build times and has a smaller core JS bundle size!"}},"context":{}}